tourBios.carHigh:
2013: Finished 35th on the PGA TOUR Canada Order of Merit while making six cuts in nine starts...Best finish was a T4 at The Great Waterway Classic in August...Was also T14 the next week at the Wildfire Invitational...Made one start on the Web.com Tour but missed the cut at the Chitimacha Louisiana Open.

2012: Played on PGA TOUR Canada...Lost in a playoff at the Dakota Dunes Casino Open.

2011: Was a member of the PGA TOUR after qualifying though the National Qualifying Tournament the previous year (finished T27)...Made 19 starts and made six cuts, with his best finish a T32 at the HP Byron Nelson Classic...Also made eight Web.com Tour starts, with two cuts made and a T33 at the Chitimacha Louisiana Open his best performance.

2010: Competed on the Canadian Tour after finishing second at the 2009 PGA TOUR Canada qualifier. A T32 in the Winn-Dixie Jacksonville Open was his first Web.com Tour start.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: A two-time Connecticut Amateur champion (2007-08)...Competed in the 2009 U.S. Amateur and advanced to match play where he won one match...Played collegiately at the University of Florida, where he was named to the All-SEC Academic Honor Roll and served as a team captain.
tourBios.personal: His earliest golf memory was coming in second in a two-man event at age five...His biggest thrill in golf was qualifying for the PGA TOUR and biggest thrill outside golf was getting married...Follows the Florida Gators, New York Yankees, the New York Knicks and the Dallas Cowboys...Never travels without his headphones and music...His superstition/lucky charm is using a No. 17 golf ball...Favorite course he's played is Pebble Beach and would love to play Augusta National...Would love to trade places for a day with LeBron James because "he's the king"...His dream foursome would include his father, Tiger Woods and Sean Connery...Carries orange Tic Tacs and Clif Bars in his bag...Favorite websites include espn.com and hotnewhiphop.com...His favorite city to visit is New York...Enjoys rap music and says if he weren't playing professional golf he'd enjoy being a rapper...Cellphone ring is "Uptown" by Drake...Enjoys Dan Brown and Ian Fleming books...Favorite TV shows include "Seinfeld" and "The League," while movie favorites include "Rounders" and any James Bond film.

tourBios.carHigh: 2010: Earned his PGA TOUR card for the first time with a T27 finish at the 2010 Qualifying Tournament. Gained his card despite a bogey on the final hole, which allowed fellow Florida Gator alum Billy Horschel to gain his card (along with Scott Gordon). Has never played in a PGA TOUR event. Finished T32 at the Winn-Dixie Jacksonville Open in his only career Nationwide Tour start. Played on the 2010 Canadian Tour, with a season-best T4 at the 2010 Desert Dunes Classic. Has also played on the NGA Hooters Tour. Amateur: Captain of the golf team during his senior season at Florida. Individual medalist at the 2009 Golden Ocala Collegiate. Winner of the 2007 and 2008 Connecticut Amateur Championship. Was T2 in stroke play qualifying at the 2009 U.S. Amateur, with a two-round total of 141 at Southern Hills CC in Tulsa, OK. Went on to win one match before dropping his second round contest.
tourBios.personal: Biggest thrill in golf was competing for the University of Florida...Favorite golf course played is Point O'Woods G&CC in Michigan. Would most like to play Augusta National...Never travels without his headphones...Favorite professional team is the New York Yankees. Favorite TV show is "Two and a Half Men."...Enjoys James Bond movies. Favorite entertainer is Drake. Enjoys Dan Brown novels...Favorite city to visit is New York. Favorite vacation spots are the Florida beaches...Would round out his dream foursome with Tiger Woods, Fred Couples and Jack Nicklaus...Played for his high school tennis and basketball teams and played multiple junior tennis tournaments before switching to golf.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA TOUR Canada was 2nd in 2012 at the Dakota Dunes Open.
